<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05103d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05103d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05103d"> 103(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> rather you than / the turbid master</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[From a letter from Cellan to Ardhelm]</font> Knowing how you excel in intellect, in Roman excellence, and in the varied flowers of letters after the Greeks, <mark>I would rather learn from your mouth, the purest font of knowledge, than drink from any other spring, especially from the turbid master</mark>. I beseech you to take me and teach me because the brightness of wisdom shines in you beyond many lecturers, and you understand the minds of foreigners who desire to acquire knowledge, for you have been to Rome &hellip; <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="IIMB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IIMB"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 260</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
